        <div xml:id="AN3">
            <lg type="edition"><l>iruṅkaḻi mutalai <choice><seg>mīntō</seg><seg>mēntō</seg></choice> laṉṉa</l>
<l>karuṅkā lōmaik kāṇpiṉ peruñciṉaik</l>
<l>kaṭiyuṭai naṉantalai yīṉṟiḷaip paṭṭa</l>
<l>koṭuvāyp <choice><seg>pēṭai</seg><seg>pēṭai<supplied>k</supplied></seg></choice> <choice><seg>kakkirai</seg><seg>kalkirai</seg></choice> tarīiya</l>
<l>māṉṟuvēṭ ṭeḻunta ceñcevi yeruvai</l>
<l>vāṉṟōy cimaiya <choice><seg>viṟaṉmalaik</seg><seg>vuyarvaraik</seg></choice> kavāaṟ</l>
<l><choice><seg>ṟuḷaṅkunaṭai</seg><seg><supplied>tu</supplied>ḷaṅkunaṭai</seg></choice> maraiyā valampaṭat tolaicci</l>
<l>yoṇceṅ kuruti yuvaṟiyuṇ ṭaruntupu</l>
<l>pulavuppuli tuṟanta kalavukkaḻi <choice><seg>kaṭimuṭaik</seg><seg>kaṭumuṭai</seg></choice></l>
<l>koḷḷai <choice><seg>māntari</seg><seg>mānta</seg></choice> <choice><seg>ṉāṉātu</seg><seg>riṉṉātu</seg></choice> kavarum</l>
<l>pullilai <choice><seg>marāatta</seg><seg>marātta</seg></choice> vakaṉcē ṇattaṅ</l>
<l>kalantara luḷḷamoṭu kaḻiyak kāṭṭip</l>
<l>piṉṉiṉṟu turakku neñca niṉvāy</l>
<l>vāypōl poymmoḻi <choice><seg>yevvaṅ</seg><seg>yemmevvaṅ</seg></choice> kaḷaiyā</l>
<l>kavirita <choice><seg>ḻaṉṉa</seg><seg>ḻaṉṉak</seg></choice> kāṇpiṉ cevvā</l>
<l>yantīṅ kiḷavi yāyiḻai maṭantai</l>
<l>koṭuṅkuḻaik kamartta nōkka</l>
<l>neṭuñcē ṇāriṭai <choice><seg>vilaṅku ñāṉṟē.</seg><seg>vilaṅku cāṉṟē.</seg></choice></l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Where the red-eared vulture, that had risen to hunt majestically</l>
<l rend="indent">	in order to bring <choice><seg>prey to be spewn up [again] by </seg><seg>lasting prey to </seg></choice> [its] hook-beaked <choice><seg>female,</seg><seg>female</seg></choice> </l>
<l rend="indent">	that was exhausted from giving birth in the protected wide range</l>
<l rend="indent">	of the big branches, pleasing to see, of the Ōmai tree with a trunk as black as</l>
<l><choice><seg>	the upper </seg><seg>	the </seg></choice> hide <choice><seg>of the crocodile </seg><seg>of the crocodile visible </seg></choice> in the dark backwaters,</l>
<l><choice><seg>	on the slope of the </seg><seg>	on the slope of the high </seg></choice> <choice><seg>mountain, victorious </seg><seg>mountain </seg></choice> with summits that touch the sky,</l>
<l>seizes as plunder, <choice><seg>unendingly </seg><seg>unpleasant </seg></choice> to the people,</l>
<l rend="indent">	the <choice><seg>strong-reeking </seg><seg>very pungent </seg></choice> flesh from a joint abandoned by the meat-reeking tiger,</l>
<l rend="indent">	after it had killed, so that it falls on [its] right side, a wild cow with swaying gait</l>
<l rend="indent">	[and] eaten [it], the bright red blood welling up,</l>
<l>the path into the wide distance of low-leafed trees,</l>
<l>showing [it] so as to pass [there], with a mind on bringing [her] ornaments,</l>
<l>o heart that stands behind [me and] urges [me on], on your part</l>
<l>the false words similar to truth do not remove [my] <choice><seg>trouble</seg><seg>trouble,</seg></choice> </l>
<l><choice><seg>– at a time when [my] </seg><seg>deserving to be blocked out, on the </seg></choice> difficult way into the long <choice><seg>distance is blocked by</seg><seg>distance,</seg></choice> </l>
<l><choice><seg></seg><seg>	by </seg></choice> the glance, at strife with the curved ear-rings,</l>
<l>of the girl with choice jewels [and] pretty sweet words,</l>
<l>with a red mouth as pleasing to see as the petals of the coral tree.</l>
<l rend="indent"></l></lg>
        </div>
    </body>
